<title>USA: Aliant Communications authorizes buyback.</title>
<headline>Aliant Communications authorizes buyback.</headline>
<dateline>LINCOLN, Neb. 1996-11-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Aliant Communications Inc said Wednesday its board authorized the repurchase of up to 400,000 shares of its common stock.</p>
<p>This is in addition to a 600,000 share authorization approved by the board on April 24, 1991. A total of 86,574 shares remain available for repurchase under that authorization.  </p>
<p>Purchases are to be made from time to time in open market or through privately negotiated transactions.</p>
<p>Repurchased shares will be returned to authorized but unissued status pending potential future issuance in connection with possible acquisitions, employee benefit, option or stock ownership plans.</p>
<p>Aliant, a communications company, has 36.5 million shares outstanding.</p>
<p>	   -- Chicago newsdesk 312 408-8787</p>
